ce:section.ce:para:
Yellow-emitting N-CDs are successfully constructed from o-phenylenediamine and dicyandiamine precursors via utilizing a convenient hydrothermal-assisted way. The synthesized N-CDs exhibit favorable solubility, high QY, superior photoluminescence and good biocompatibility, which facilitate their capable of biological imaging. In addition, the fluorescent of N-CDs (F/F

                        0
                     ) displays a well linear response towards 4-NP concentration (0.1–39 μM), corresponding to the LOD as low as 0.05 μM. Based on the outstanding analytical performance, a 4-NP-detection method is established and applied to actual water samples, along with the recoveries of 98.75–101.50 and RSD of 1.56–2.50 (n = 5), illustrating that our probe is ideal for analysing 4-NP quantitatively in real samples.
